headline: Ashley Snyder Joins Medical Home Network as Chief Development Officer to Lead Partnership Efforts
summary: Medical Home Network (MHN), a mission-driven organization enabling federally qualified health centers (FQHCs) nationwide to succeed in value-based care, today announced the appointment of Ashley Snyder as its first Chief Development Officer.

headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid DVA and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, DaVita’s shares (currently trading at $146.05) have posted a disappointing 14% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 3.1% gain. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
